  For a prime \(w\nmid p\) split in \(K\), the local dual \(H^1(K_w,M_\theta)^\vee\) is \(\Lambda\)-torsion with characteristic ideal generated by \(\mathcal{P}_w(\theta)\). In particular, \(H^1(K_w,M_\theta)^\vee\) has \(\mu=0\).

  \textit{Proof idea.} The key point is that \(w\) is finitely decomposed in \(K_\infty/K\), so the local cohomology is governed by the unramified quotient of inertia. The characteristic ideal is the local Euler factor, and therefore no nontrivial \(\mu\)-part can appear.
\end{lemma}

